member.summary:
This method clears the time span that should be drawn, instead everything
from this trial is drawn or resets the time span to the time line duration,
depending on the parameter

This static method creates a new raw data table for
the given subject with the name [subjectNameRawdata]
using the SQL Statement:
CREATE TABLE [" + subjectName + "Rawdata]([ID] [bigint] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
[SubjectName] [varchar](50) COLLATE Latin1_General_CI_AS NOT NULL,
[TrialID] [int] NOT NULL,[Time][bigint] NOT NULL,[PupilDiaX] [float] NULL,
[PupilDiaY][float] NULL,[GazePosX] [float] NULL,[GazePosY] [float] NULL,
[MousePosX][float] NULL,[MousePosY] [float] NULL,[EventID] [int] NULL,
CONSTRAINT[PK_" + subjectName + "Rawdata]PRIMARY KEY CLUSTERED(
/// [ID] ASC)WITH(PAD_INDEX = OFF,IGNORE_DUP_KEY = OFF)ON [PRIMARY])ON[PRIMARY];";

Deletes the raw data table for the given subject from the database
using the SQL statement:
DROP TABLE [" + Subject + "Rawdata];

member.remarks:
This change has to be afterwards written to the database file
            with a call to 
            Queries.CreateRawDataTableInDB(subjectName);
            Queries.WriteRawDataWithBulkStatement(subjectName);

member.value:
A  that is true,
            if import should ignore lines, with less columns, than in first data row,
            otherwise false.

member.summary:
Gets or sets a value indicating whether 
import should ignore lines,
that don´t start with a numeral

member.value:
A  that is true,
            if import should ignore lines, hat don´t start with a numeral,
            otherwise false.

A  that is true,
            if import should ignore lines, commented with character ,
            otherwise false.

A  that is true,
            if import should only use lines, commented with character ,
            otherwise false.

A  that is true,
            if import should ignore lines containing ,
            otherwise false.

A  that is true,
            if column titles are in the first data row,
            otherwise false.

member.param:
True
            if dialog should return true, if subjects was found in the database,
            otherwise false.

member.summary:
This method steps through each of the stop conditions of the current slide.
  If any of them matches the current state, check for
  response correctness and set bChangeStimulus=true;

member.param:
True,
            if the column headers should be reread from the parsed file,
            if the should be saved as they currently are, false.
